                    "3. PP2C phosphatase inhibited → SnRK2 kinase active",
                    "4. SnRK2 activates anion channels → Cl⁻ and malate leave guard cells",
                    "5. K⁺ efflux channels also activated → K⁺ leaves",
                    "6. Ca²⁺ released as second messenger, reinforcing channel activity",
                    "7. Solute loss → water potential of guard cells rises → water exits by osmosis",
                    "8. Turgor pressure falls → guard cells become flaccid → stomata close"
