                    "2. When fertilised heavily → tall stems lodge (fall over) before harvest",
                    "3. Green Revolution varieties carry Rht (wheat) or sd1 (rice) gene mutations",
                    "4. Rht encodes modified DELLA proteins insensitive to GA-mediated degradation",
                    "5. DELLA continuously represses GA responses → short internodes → dwarf plants",
                    "6. Dwarf plants withstand wind and their own weight with heavy fertilisation",
                    "7. More resources directed to grain → higher yield → transformed food production globally"
