                    "3. PKA phosphorylates phosphorylase kinase → activates glycogen phosphorylase → glycogenolysis",
                    "4. PKA phosphorylates glycogen synthase → inactivation → glycogen synthesis stops",
                    "5. Liver: glucose released into blood; muscle: glucose used locally for contraction",
                    "6. PKA also activates hormone-sensitive lipase → lipolysis → FFA + glycerol released"
