                    aka: "DOMS",
                    definition: "Muscle pain and stiffness peaking 24–72 hours after unaccustomed or eccentric exercise",
                    cause: "Micro-tears in myofibrils and connective tissue → inflammation → nociceptor activation; NOT lactic acid",
