                        cicr: "Calcium-Induced Calcium Release — small Ca²⁺ influx via L-type channels triggers massive Ca²⁺ release from SR via RyR2 (spark → fire analogy)",
                        refractoryPeriod: "Long absolute refractory period (~200 ms) prevents tetanus — essential for pump function"
